Author:  HODDER
Vol / Page:  72
Edition:
Quote:  That night I enjoyed - what had often pleased me to read of in books - a bush-fire. Six or seven large old dry trees had been chopped down and cast onto the already large fire , which threw out a capital heat and lit up the whole of the bush surrounding us.
