Vol / Page:  2/vi/64
Edition:  1889,1974
Quote:  By the side of the creek, the Grey Party ... pitched their tent. Of course they lit a bush fire. They rolled huge logs into it, and piled branches of odiferous gum-trees on it, until it blazed high up into the brilliant atmosphere.
